# Batch clean up of Work Exception Logs

[!include [banner](../includes/banner.md)]

The functionality for batch clean up job of work exception logs lets
you remove these logs by using a batch job.

## Where it applies

For this functionality, work exception logs are removed by a
batch job given a specific criteria. This functionality is useful when you want to remove old work exception logs that might be impacting the performance of your system (e.g. searching for locations with open work exceptions).

## How it is set up

### Specify cleanup criteria for work exception logs

To access the cleanup dialog, navigate to **Warehouse management \> Periodic Tasks \> Clean up \> Clean up work exception logs**).

Select which exception logs should be removed, **Open** or **Closed** (default: Closed), how many days older than today should be kept (default: 30). A maximum number of records to be removed can be specified as well to minimize impact in the system (default: 100000).

Other configurations such as recurrence, alerts and batch group can be configured as well.

Once the job has finished execution a message notifying how many records were removed will be displayed.

